      "seed": 345830139,
      "version": 102,
      "versionNonce": 1775735694,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How do we list a file -> ls command\nHow do we see a running process -> ps  command",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How do we list a file -> ls command\nHow do we see a running process -> ps  command",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "GM8vTfBa_dtD4EQz5KCp6",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 997.3604207963419,
      "y": 67439.47365205291,
      "width": 110,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjv",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 692854421,
      "version": 16,
      "versionNonce": 1875358802,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Docker -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Docker -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "l2cqf0o62HY1p54G0_sSv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1040.919014546342,
      "y": 67480.74708955291,
      "width": 1078,
      "height": 1075,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjw",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1941121851,
      "version": 1523,
      "versionNonce": 419033550,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. docker --version -> to see the version\n\n2. we need to check service of docker is running or not, demon process is running or not, so that\nit keeps on supporting containers. for that we need to run command\nA daemon process is:\n    A background process that runs continuously and handles system or service-level tasks without \n    user interaction.\nsystemctl status docker\nif not active run\nsystemctl start docker\nsystemctl enable docker\n\n3. Check do we have any container or not\n    docker ps -> all blank\n    or\n    docker container ps\n\n4 Check do we have docker images or not\n    docker ls\n    or\n    docker images\n    or \n    docker image ls\n\n\n    docker container commands like \n    docker container ls\n    images\n    docker image ls\n    for all container commands they are writing container\n    for all image commands they are writing image\n    but without this also older version also works\n\n5 Run container\n    docker run ubuntu:latest\n    \n    if now we will do docker container ps -> it will not show\n    since container is running process, it should be visible using ps command\n    \n    docker ps -a -> here we will see the container but that status is exit, which means our \n        continer spin up hua, start hua and it immediately died and we got our shell back because\n        it has nothing to do, we have given no task, no process, nothing to do. So it exited.\n        Now we will try to run in such a way that it will run for sometime.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. docker --version -> to see the version\n\n2. we need to check service of docker is running or not, demon process is running or not, so that\nit keeps on supporting containers. for that we need to run command\nA daemon process is:\n    A background process that runs continuously and handles system or service-level tasks without \n    user interaction.\nsystemctl status docker\nif not active run\nsystemctl start docker\nsystemctl enable docker\n\n3. Check do we have any container or not\n    docker ps -> all blank\n    or\n    docker container ps\n\n4 Check do we have docker images or not\n    docker ls\n    or\n    docker images\n    or \n    docker image ls\n\n\n    docker container commands like \n    docker container ls\n    images\n    docker image ls\n    for all container commands they are writing container\n    for all image commands they are writing image\n    but without this also older version also works\n\n5 Run container\n    docker run ubuntu:latest\n    \n    if now we will do docker container ps -> it will not show\n    since container is running process, it should be visible using ps command\n    \n    docker ps -a -> here we will see the container but that status is exit, which means our \n        continer spin up hua, start hua and it immediately died and we got our shell back because\n        it has nothing to do, we have given no task, no process, nothing to do. So it exited.\n        Now we will try to run in such a way that it will run for sometime.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "dONLvfaoI5tglOdo1RdrY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1071.501045796342,
      "y": 68560.67287080291,
      "width": 836,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjx",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2000790875,
      "version": 146,
      "versionNonce": 20011538,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Interesting part is ubuntu:latest chala kaise, we were not having any image?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Interesting part is ubuntu:latest chala kaise, we were not having any image?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "I5FujG6ku5JE2dWhP4SNx",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1125.422920796342,
      "y": 68596.92677705291,
      "width": 1100,
      "height": 575,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjy",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1985062581,
      "version": 1903,
      "versionNonce": 1756792846,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker image ls -> it will show the ubuntu:latest image\n\nDocker is created in a very interesting way, Solomon Hikes creator of Docker when he created, he\nnoticed this problem already existing with LXC, if image is not there, then bring the image and \nthen start a container, so he automated everything\n\nIf we are willing to run something. It will first check in our system if the image is there or\nnot, If it is not there it will pull the image from internet and obviously it can't search whole\ninternet, So when we run the command on our system, System goes online on a very specific location,\nthis location is called as our docker repository. And this repo can be of diff types, like we\ncan have the s3 bucket where we can keep all docker images, we can call it as our own repository,\nWe can make one in our system or in a diff system which storage is shared.\nThere is a public repo also that exists out there. So if we want to publically keep our images\nopen to all we can put over there as well. s3 or anything in which we are putting our images  is\nprivate repo, But the public repo of docker that exists out there is called as dockerhub.\n\nSo it will go to Dockerhub,by default docker hub location is already there in docker configuration\nand it will search for ubuntu:latest, if it is publically available, because it is available it will\npull it from dockerhub and create a container from it. But once pulled it will show in docker images\ncommand.\n\nSummary -> if the image is not in our system it will try to pull from dockerhub if we run \n    docker run command.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker image ls -> it will show the ubuntu:latest image\n\nDocker is created in a very interesting way, Solomon Hikes creator of Docker when he created, he\nnoticed this problem already existing with LXC, if image is not there, then bring the image and \nthen start a container, so he automated everything\n\nIf we are willing to run something. It will first check in our system if the image is there or\nnot, If it is not there it will pull the image from internet and obviously it can't search whole\ninternet, So when we run the command on our system, System goes online on a very specific location,\nthis location is called as our docker repository. And this repo can be of diff types, like we\ncan have the s3 bucket where we can keep all docker images, we can call it as our own repository,\nWe can make one in our system or in a diff system which storage is shared.\nThere is a public repo also that exists out there. So if we want to publically keep our images\nopen to all we can put over there as well. s3 or anything in which we are putting our images  is\nprivate repo, But the public repo of docker that exists out there is called as dockerhub.\n\nSo it will go to Dockerhub,by default docker hub location is already there in docker configuration\nand it will search for ubuntu:latest, if it is publically available, because it is available it will\npull it from dockerhub and create a container from it. But once pulled it will show in docker images\ncommand.\n\nSummary -> if the image is not in our system it will try to pull from dockerhub if we run \n    docker run command.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "zP2lZeS8Y9qaqAVD9HhjA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1001.3604207963419,
      "y": 69254.04396455291,
      "width": 1177,
      "height": 1175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjz",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 941020117,
      "version": 2646,
      "versionNonce": 165693394,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "6. To Make sure Container is not exiting and it is actually runnning, we will give some flags\n    over here\n    \n    docker run -it ubuntu:latest -> Now we will see we will inside the container not inside our\n                    base machine.\n        hostname -i -> this will give us the ip address and we can check it with our base system\n                both public and private ip address that those IPs are different and this IP is \n                different. which means we are in a different system, It is not technically a \n                entirely diff system, It is just a virtual space create within our VM\n\n        exit -> exit from container\n\n    \n    Now if we will check docker ps -> it will not be there soon we have come out from our container\n        it stops\n\n    -it -> interactive terminal -> Means I want a terminal and I want it in a interactive manner. Which\n        means I can keep on giving commands, It will keep on giving me output untill and unless we tell\n            our terminal to stop. But when we ask for stop everything done, container will be exited.\n        because container bnd hote hi it has nothing to do. So it will stop and exit itself.\n    \n    if we want keep on running then we can give flag\n\n    -dit -> we can give d in any order like itd or idt, d stands for d foreground, basically it is telling\n            that run the container but in background\n\n    docker run -dit ubuntu:latest \n    docker ps -> now it will show container having image ubuntu:latest is up and running, but the\n            container is running in background rather than foreground, which means now we have\n            our terminal but container is running in background\n\n    docker run -it ubuntu:latest -> now we will be in different container\n    ctrl + p +q -> it will exit from container but will not stop container and now we will be in base shell\n    docker ps -> here it will show both containers are up and running.\n\n    -dit -> basically detaching the terminal\n\n\n7. Right now we are getting images by running the container. What is we dont want to run\n    a container but we want image in our system.\n    \n    So to do this we will pull the image from DockerHub\n    to pull image from dockerHub\n\n    docker pull ubuntu:14.04 -> it will pull the image from dockerhub with version 14.04\n    docker pull nginx\n    docker images -> it will list all the images ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "6. To Make sure Container is not exiting and it is actually runnning, we will give some flags\n    over here\n    \n    docker run -it ubuntu:latest -> Now we will see we will inside the container not inside our\n                    base machine.\n        hostname -i -> this will give us the ip address and we can check it with our base system\n                both public and private ip address that those IPs are different and this IP is \n                different. which means we are in a different system, It is not technically a \n                entirely diff system, It is just a virtual space create within our VM\n\n        exit -> exit from container\n\n    \n    Now if we will check docker ps -> it will not be there soon we have come out from our container\n        it stops\n\n    -it -> interactive terminal -> Means I want a terminal and I want it in a interactive manner. Which\n        means I can keep on giving commands, It will keep on giving me output untill and unless we tell\n            our terminal to stop. But when we ask for stop everything done, container will be exited.\n        because container bnd hote hi it has nothing to do. So it will stop and exit itself.\n    \n    if we want keep on running then we can give flag\n\n    -dit -> we can give d in any order like itd or idt, d stands for d foreground, basically it is telling\n            that run the container but in background\n\n    docker run -dit ubuntu:latest \n    docker ps -> now it will show container having image ubuntu:latest is up and running, but the\n            container is running in background rather than foreground, which means now we have\n            our terminal but container is running in background\n\n    docker run -it ubuntu:latest -> now we will be in different container\n    ctrl + p +q -> it will exit from container but will not stop container and now we will be in base shell\n    docker ps -> here it will show both containers are up and running.\n\n    -dit -> basically detaching the terminal\n\n\n7. Right now we are getting images by running the container. What is we dont want to run\n    a container but we want image in our system.\n    \n    So to do this we will pull the image from DockerHub\n    to pull image from dockerHub\n\n    docker pull ubuntu:14.04 -> it will pull the image from dockerhub with version 14.04\n    docker pull nginx\n    docker images -> it will list all the images ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "HarqiC0I3Jc5CHMq_QuuC",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1046.149483296342,
