      "seed": 1358159829,
      "version": 63,
      "versionNonce": 46292110,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How we will deal with running containers? -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How we will deal with running containers? -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "sAm7C2S-iJEBRLBPRrjZb",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1179.514717671342,
      "y": 71108.62599580291,
      "width": 1089,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 727234517,
      "version": 223,
      "versionNonce": 1183447890,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "If there is a running container which is not in exit state, so the command is to put that container\ninto exit state is\n\ndocker stop container_id/container_name",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "If there is a running container which is not in exit state, so the command is to put that container\ninto exit state is\n\ndocker stop container_id/container_name",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "y6N6hCT1-eRYBAEV-QYwG",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1177.877998921342,
      "y": 71253.78224580291,
      "width": 1056,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 878295157,
      "version": 662,
      "versionNonce": 1000577742,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "containers are more like machines, after stoping also we can still reuse it. whenever we want\nwe can restart that.\n\ndocker start container_id \n\nwhat if we dont want shut down due to after shut down it is still holding on some memory, it is\nstill there as a process but the process is not active. So it has some space of mine, so we dont\nwant that space, So if we want to take away that space also.\n\ndocker kill container_id -> Now this running container will be in exit status.\n\ndocker ps -q -> it will list id of all running containers",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "containers are more like machines, after stoping also we can still reuse it. whenever we want\nwe can restart that.\n\ndocker start container_id \n\nwhat if we dont want shut down due to after shut down it is still holding on some memory, it is\nstill there as a process but the process is not active. So it has some space of mine, so we dont\nwant that space, So if we want to take away that space also.\n\ndocker kill container_id -> Now this running container will be in exit status.\n\ndocker ps -q -> it will list id of all running containers",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "2bvYYsp7C7EXGhDCECvZf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1106.026436421342,
      "y": 71567.85255830291,
      "width": 275,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 627634101,
      "version": 37,
      "versionNonce": 1980940562,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Pruning of a Container ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Pruning of a Container ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "pugboj0okyAORpfF1dDfa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1181.706123921342,
      "y": 71624.00490205291,
      "width": 1045,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk8",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 909328539,
      "version": 152,
      "versionNonce": 977473806,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker container prune -> it will delete all the containers that we have, It will prune all the\n            stopped or exited containers.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker container prune -> it will delete all the containers that we have, It will prune all the\n            stopped or exited containers.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "DySSyNAjOBflh25lehnDD",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1188.780342671342,
      "y": 71741.67287080291,
      "width": 1067,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk9",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1537619925,
      "version": 628,
      "versionNonce": 1274859218,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Pruning means if there are stopped or exited containers that we anyways dont need, why to keep \nthem and this can be with containers, this can be with images, this can be done with volumes,\nnetworks, so many things related to Docker.\n\nafter docker container pruner\ndocker ps -a -> we dont see any exited container\n\nbut if we have to remove a very specific container not from shutdown state, but we have to remove\nit forever then we do\n\ndocker rm container_id -> it will only remove if container is not running",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Pruning means if there are stopped or exited containers that we anyways dont need, why to keep \nthem and this can be with containers, this can be with images, this can be done with volumes,\nnetworks, so many things related to Docker.\n\nafter docker container pruner\ndocker ps -a -> we dont see any exited container\n\nbut if we have to remove a very specific container not from shutdown state, but we have to remove\nit forever then we do\n\ndocker rm container_id -> it will only remove if container is not running",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "fg0OViqC_HRTB96JbNUi9",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 977.6944051713419,
      "y": 72122.23537080291,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkA",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 560892891,
      "version": 98,
      "versionNonce": 437894990,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Containers are very fast and efficient way to spin up a VM. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Containers are very fast and efficient way to spin up a VM. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "91fDffCE5l49k42Q7t0--",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 978.3897176713419,
      "y": 72178.18068330291,
      "width": 990,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
