      "version": 118,
      "versionNonce": 2094998674,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Containarizing is not a proble in Industry now, because every one using Docker now a days.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Containarizing is not a proble in Industry now, because every one using Docker now a days.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "4P4pRUJyVbIWH6nNwaeG4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 977.6006551713419,
      "y": 72263.67287080291,
      "width": 1320,
      "height": 775,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkC",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1747258165,
      "version": 2835,
      "versionNonce": 528524686,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Containere are  not taking that much of RAM or any other hardware resource, that is not being consumed, So \nrather than spinning of one container people started launching multiple, And this always happens because\nwhen we have to scale our infra, scaling infra means we can catter more users. Faster scaling and efficient\nscaling means even more users. If we have to grow the user, ultimately we have to grow the number of\ncontainers as well. So prolem comes in the industry container management, there are multiple container now\nwe need to manage all , manage means in terms of how will multiple applications stay in multiple container\nSuppoer we have container runnning Application A, B, C, D, and now we want to change the containers that are\nrunning application B. This is one issue.\n\nIf we want to run multiple applications together, how will we separate them inside a single container Or \ninside a single machine which is running 2 containers, How will we separate them? that is another issue\n\nCommunication between two application or microservices that became a issue.\n\nNetworking and Security became the issue\n\nMostly when the containers are going down and coming up, then what is happening, which application is\ngoing down and which application is coming up?\nSo it is more like balancing between so many containers. So there are n containers and we are trying to \nbalance which one will come up and which one will be go down at what time.\nIt is more like there are n people, and they want to play different instrument, different instrument in \nour case is diff applications. and what we are trying to do over here as a developer or Devops engineer\nis who is controlling all of them or managing all of them or the another word over here is called as\norchestrating.\nFor Orchestration the tool in industry which is used is called as Kubernetes(K8S because 8 characters in between K & S).\nDocker also give solution for this like docker compose, another thing docker swam both of these have their\nown usecases, but we dont need to read them. Because industry is not using docker compose and docker swam.\nwe have better better version of this in form of K8S or also called as kubernetes. and we will see this later on.\n\nKubernetes is not only used for Docker container, it can be use for any hypervisor or any container. and it is \norchestrating containers.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Containere are  not taking that much of RAM or any other hardware resource, that is not being consumed, So \nrather than spinning of one container people started launching multiple, And this always happens because\nwhen we have to scale our infra, scaling infra means we can catter more users. Faster scaling and efficient\nscaling means even more users. If we have to grow the user, ultimately we have to grow the number of\ncontainers as well. So prolem comes in the industry container management, there are multiple container now\nwe need to manage all , manage means in terms of how will multiple applications stay in multiple container\nSuppoer we have container runnning Application A, B, C, D, and now we want to change the containers that are\nrunning application B. This is one issue.\n\nIf we want to run multiple applications together, how will we separate them inside a single container Or \ninside a single machine which is running 2 containers, How will we separate them? that is another issue\n\nCommunication between two application or microservices that became a issue.\n\nNetworking and Security became the issue\n\nMostly when the containers are going down and coming up, then what is happening, which application is\ngoing down and which application is coming up?\nSo it is more like balancing between so many containers. So there are n containers and we are trying to \nbalance which one will come up and which one will be go down at what time.\nIt is more like there are n people, and they want to play different instrument, different instrument in \nour case is diff applications. and what we are trying to do over here as a developer or Devops engineer\nis who is controlling all of them or managing all of them or the another word over here is called as\norchestrating.\nFor Orchestration the tool in industry which is used is called as Kubernetes(K8S because 8 characters in between K & S).\nDocker also give solution for this like docker compose, another thing docker swam both of these have their\nown usecases, but we dont need to read them. Because industry is not using docker compose and docker swam.\nwe have better better version of this in form of K8S or also called as kubernetes. and we will see this later on.\n\nKubernetes is not only used for Docker container, it can be use for any hypervisor or any container. and it is \norchestrating containers.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Nixbr7vTCqLaczFw-IQjW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 983.0928426713419,
      "y": 73114.67287080291,
      "width": 869,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkG",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 126610011,
      "version": 321,
      "versionNonce": 309379666,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker images -> all the images\ndocker ps -> all the running containers\ndocker ps -q -> all the running containers id\n\ndocker kill $(docker ps -q) -> it will kill all the running containers\n\ndocker rmi $(docker ps -q) -> it will remove all the images that are not in use",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker images -> all the images\ndocker ps -> all the running containers\ndocker ps -q -> all the running containers id\n\ndocker kill $(docker ps -q) -> it will kill all the running containers\n\ndocker rmi $(docker ps -q) -> it will remove all the images that are not in use",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "IwWU5V85UHv_-J_AThPdA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 972.1358114213419,
      "y": 73366.20412080291,
      "width": 693,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1786906677,
      "version": 78,
      "versionNonce": 464569294,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We can give name to our container also, we can't remember id ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We can give name to our container also, we can't remember id ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ID83qWMVsiwSkGggEMjHQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1021.7647176713419,
      "y": 73419.70412080291,
      "width": 495,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
