      "seed": 2096550741,
      "version": 41,
      "versionNonce": 1577739086,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How it will reach to container?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How it will reach to container?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "IddOb6yfEvV2di29YbAqX",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1514.741280171342,
      "y": 75079.65333955291,
      "width": 880,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkp",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 446826773,
      "version": 577,
      "versionNonce": 683327634,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "To make it reach to container, what we do is internally whatever request\nis coming to different port number like 8080, when I will get request from\n8080 we will redirect it to container's port number 80. and container's port\n80 has a web server already running or VM ka port 80. this can be done\nVM to VM, base to base, base to VM it can work any ways. When we get request on \n1 port number, we forward it to another that is called patting",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "To make it reach to container, what we do is internally whatever request\nis coming to different port number like 8080, when I will get request from\n8080 we will redirect it to container's port number 80. and container's port\n80 has a web server already running or VM ka port 80. this can be done\nVM to VM, base to base, base to VM it can work any ways. When we get request on \n1 port number, we forward it to another that is called patting",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ls1sAWJ0IyR0yYLKsRxQE",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1074.897530171342,
      "y": 75357.50880830291,
      "width": 462,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkr",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1484327035,
      "version": 52,
      "versionNonce": 1706871182,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How we will do it in Docker Container? -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How we will do it in Docker Container? -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Me-rQTHsD0y7uPlFUg39S",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1143.518623921342,
      "y": 75398.09474580291,
      "width": 1166,
      "height": 500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bks",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1515397525,
      "version": 778,
      "versionNonce": 2021187154,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Launch a Nginx container, that can be used as web server not a good aproach but can be used as\na web server.\n\ndocker run -d nginx -> nginx container is running in background\n\nNow we will install a networking software(net-tools) on our base system\napt-get install net-tools\n\nnet-tools is a pack of multiple softwares, there is one software that we use here is netstat, netstat show\nus all the thing that are going on for tcp and udp port.\n\nsudo netstat -tnlp -> it will show us tcp services running\nsudo netstat -unlp -> it will show us udp services runing\nsudo netstat -tunlp -> it will show all tcp and udp services running\n\nRight now we are concerned with tcp service\n\nrun\nsudo netstat -tnlp\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Launch a Nginx container, that can be used as web server not a good aproach but can be used as\na web server.\n\ndocker run -d nginx -> nginx container is running in background\n\nNow we will install a networking software(net-tools) on our base system\napt-get install net-tools\n\nnet-tools is a pack of multiple softwares, there is one software that we use here is netstat, netstat show\nus all the thing that are going on for tcp and udp port.\n\nsudo netstat -tnlp -> it will show us tcp services running\nsudo netstat -unlp -> it will show us udp services runing\nsudo netstat -tunlp -> it will show all tcp and udp services running\n\nRight now we are concerned with tcp service\n\nrun\nsudo netstat -tnlp\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "PBufqoLyQHjEeidOwfGYR",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1145.420967671342,
      "y": 75924.57912080291,
      "width": 814,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bku",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1613354197,
      "version": 94,
      "versionNonce": 248014798,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646398,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Now we have anyway to reach till port 80? Can we reach our here by someway",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Now we have anyway to reach till port 80? Can we reach our here by someway",
      "autoResize": true,
