    {
      "id": "nL0dQr_-HVuba6mJdMfM3",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2305.2022176713417,
      "y": 84999.32651663624,
      "width": 286,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bm2",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1664362029,
      "version": 196,
      "versionNonce": 1653243150,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "This is called as\nMulti layered architecture",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "This is called as\nMulti layered architecture",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "K7vpkdtalizMmaz16f_Lu",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1485.4834676713417,
      "y": 85278.16636038624,
      "width": 1166,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bm3",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 342695117,
      "version": 691,
      "versionNonce": 1060250322,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Because of this multi layer architecture, our size of image becoming bigger and bigger. So our ultimate\ngoal when we are creating dockerfile is to reduce the number of layers as much as we can. lesser the\nlayers are smaller the size of our final docker image. Smaller is the size of final dockerimage, faster is\ndeployment. And that is why we use docker image because they are small, fast. So we always tend to reduce\nthe size.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Because of this multi layer architecture, our size of image becoming bigger and bigger. So our ultimate\ngoal when we are creating dockerfile is to reduce the number of layers as much as we can. lesser the\nlayers are smaller the size of our final docker image. Smaller is the size of final dockerimage, faster is\ndeployment. And that is why we use docker image because they are small, fast. So we always tend to reduce\nthe size.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "LVLOgEyDMaZqXG-rP4hWs",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1478.6084676713417,
      "y": 83458.12599580291,
      "width": 1309,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bm4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2000714893,
      "version": 1293,
      "versionNonce": 512994126,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "RUN command is packing image that is making sence, All the software installation is nothing but the file or code\nthat we are getting, but when we do service apache2 start, it is basically a process that we are running, and if we are\nrunning a process and then I make a image out of it which means a file, this makes no sence, due to after being a file\nit is somewhere in HDD, not even running anything, so would not make any sence, It will only make sence when it is a \nrunning machine, which means it is a container, So what we do is that now this service command will not give it in RUN\nwill choose a diff keyword over here which is CMD, and this is where we get Interview question\nWhen we create a container we expose the PORT 80 so that at that time PORT mapping or patting can be done.\nLike base 80 to container 80 that patting can be done and it is allowed, So basiclly we are allowing the \nfirewall to get public connections on PORT 80.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "RUN command is packing image that is making sence, All the software installation is nothing but the file or code\nthat we are getting, but when we do service apache2 start, it is basically a process that we are running, and if we are\nrunning a process and then I make a image out of it which means a file, this makes no sence, due to after being a file\nit is somewhere in HDD, not even running anything, so would not make any sence, It will only make sence when it is a \nrunning machine, which means it is a container, So what we do is that now this service command will not give it in RUN\nwill choose a diff keyword over here which is CMD, and this is where we get Interview question\nWhen we create a container we expose the PORT 80 so that at that time PORT mapping or patting can be done.\nLike base 80 to container 80 that patting can be done and it is allowed, So basiclly we are allowing the \nfirewall to get public connections on PORT 80.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "7bAtB7J5g2d9O525wHJPf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1483.3076864213417,
      "y": 83728.11427705291,
      "width": 429,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bm6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1979797805,
      "version": 92,
      "versionNonce": 105511058,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q What is the diff between RUN and CMD?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q What is the diff between RUN and CMD?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "tU5YjMxaQ5MmZP5f98Uyf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1511.5772176713417,
      "y": 83776.46193330291,
      "width": 1100,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bm7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 853256717,
      "version": 450,
      "versionNonce": 1440551310,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "this RUN is not the docker run, this RUN is a RUN which we are giving inside a dockerfile.\nRUN will run at the time of creation of image, But in CMD whatever parameter we are giving it will \nexecute it at the time of creation of the container, when the container is created, then CMD will be\nexecuted basically we are trying to put something in the start boot of the container.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "this RUN is not the docker run, this RUN is a RUN which we are giving inside a dockerfile.\nRUN will run at the time of creation of image, But in CMD whatever parameter we are giving it will \nexecute it at the time of creation of the container, when the container is created, then CMD will be\nexecuted basically we are trying to put something in the start boot of the container.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "I8TEEBQqvB1fTTa891iK1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1440.6592489213417,
      "y": 83216.30568330291,
      "width": 363,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
