      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "then rather pulling from dockerhub we can configure in our system, not in container, in our\nbase system where we have installed docker, in the configurations of docker",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "then rather pulling from dockerhub we can configure in our system, not in container, in our\nbase system where we have installed docker, in the configurations of docker",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "dwFCgO9-ybumMQ0c0l5UZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1621.391555550711,
      "y": 90439.376544519,
      "width": 517,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bo4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 102659539,
      "version": 55,
      "versionNonce": 1511043410,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Where do we have configuration file of docker ?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Where do we have configuration file of docker ?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "yRIgPD7O-GBF2XboPwiXW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1679.6304449343945,
      "y": 90470.08195012264,
      "width": 1067,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bo5",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1678049075,
      "version": 518,
      "versionNonce": 294339790,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "in /etc, somewhere there will be a docker folder, inside that there will be some config file,\nit this config file I wil go and replace the link of dockerhub with a new link now, that link\ncan be S3 bucket or some cloud location or any storage location that we have, And from that\nstorage location now it will see that the images exist or not. If the image is there it will pull\nand launch the container from that particular image. this is called as private repo.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "in /etc, somewhere there will be a docker folder, inside that there will be some config file,\nit this config file I wil go and replace the link of dockerhub with a new link now, that link\ncan be S3 bucket or some cloud location or any storage location that we have, And from that\nstorage location now it will see that the images exist or not. If the image is there it will pull\nand launch the container from that particular image. this is called as private repo.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "C7to9Pvl5aahY8q_aIUAL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1537.7435000067978,
      "y": 90696.62798000588,
      "width": 1232,
      "height": 550,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bo6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1711046419,
      "version": 1605,
      "versionNonce": 324187922,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker run -it ubuntu:latest -> interactive terminal we can work, we will be inside the container here\ndocker run -dit ubuntu:latest -> container will run in background(d foreground state)\ndocker attach container_id -> using this we will be inside this container, now we can do whatever we want\n                like nginx setup and all\nctrl + p + q ->  this allow the container to keep on running in background.\n\nNow lets say our container is setup , server is setup, firewalls are setup what next?\nin company level lets say we have a VM, we don't configure a whole VM and then start using it, we configure\na VM as per our need, we install everything that we need in the VM, then from this VM we create a Image, in\nterms of AWS we have created AMI, and this image is used further to create multiple instances of this and attach\nthem behine something called as Load balancer.\nOnce we have running container we try to create images from it\n\nusing docker images we are not getting file whihc we can export, may be we need files that we can ls and see\nso that, that file we can mail someday to someone, and on their system now they can use that, now they can\nuse that file, so for that it has to be a exportable file, so we make a exportable file. this exportable\nfile can be made by running container also and can be made by image also.\n\nSo we create 3 things, \ncontainer or image or exportable file\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker run -it ubuntu:latest -> interactive terminal we can work, we will be inside the container here\ndocker run -dit ubuntu:latest -> container will run in background(d foreground state)\ndocker attach container_id -> using this we will be inside this container, now we can do whatever we want\n                like nginx setup and all\nctrl + p + q ->  this allow the container to keep on running in background.\n\nNow lets say our container is setup , server is setup, firewalls are setup what next?\nin company level lets say we have a VM, we don't configure a whole VM and then start using it, we configure\na VM as per our need, we install everything that we need in the VM, then from this VM we create a Image, in\nterms of AWS we have created AMI, and this image is used further to create multiple instances of this and attach\nthem behine something called as Load balancer.\nOnce we have running container we try to create images from it\n\nusing docker images we are not getting file whihc we can export, may be we need files that we can ls and see\nso that, that file we can mail someday to someone, and on their system now they can use that, now they can\nuse that file, so for that it has to be a exportable file, so we make a exportable file. this exportable\nfile can be made by running container also and can be made by image also.\n\nSo we create 3 things, \ncontainer or image or exportable file\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "pp5fch16BDgxo_kHsIOt2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1531.14972315691,
      "y": 91290.22752237903,
      "width": 363,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bo7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 124490259,
      "version": 43,
      "versionNonce": 161839886,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How do we create our own image ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How do we create our own image ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "O1gPmzGw0oaLF8ru10BSQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1570.6059670010814,
      "y": 91320.26168068076,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bo8",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2087135325,
      "version": 764,
      "versionNonce": 1775109330,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "To create our own image, the first thing that we do , we have a running container\nthen we run docker commit for creating image from running container then we run one follow up command\ndocker tag.\ncommit + tag ->output of this is an image file\nwhen we create container either for production, test or stage, we will see containers are not designed\nin one go, we will make one change then another change, then more addition for this we keep on \ncreating versions\n\nwe run \ndocker run -it ubuntu:latest -> latest define pull image whatever latest version of ubuntu, if we want\nspecific version we can give that also like ubuntu:14.04",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "To create our own image, the first thing that we do , we have a running container\nthen we run docker commit for creating image from running container then we run one follow up command\ndocker tag.\ncommit + tag ->output of this is an image file\nwhen we create container either for production, test or stage, we will see containers are not designed\nin one go, we will make one change then another change, then more addition for this we keep on \ncreating versions\n\nwe run \ndocker run -it ubuntu:latest -> latest define pull image whatever latest version of ubuntu, if we want\nspecific version we can give that also like ubuntu:14.04",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
