      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "u_-44nudEgpigo_kfkQb3",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1613.1319393601057,
      "y": 92389.8533920535,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boK",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1405078525,
      "version": 237,
      "versionNonce": 1532844174,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We can never create a container directly, exported container first need to be converted in a image, to\nconvert in image we use the command\n\nimport\nthen we run docker run then we get a container.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We can never create a container directly, exported container first need to be converted in a image, to\nconvert in image we use the command\n\nimport\nthen we run docker run then we get a container.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "V4G_1SOVXiJM0dIpkNuU3",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1444.6938892647588,
      "y": 92632.4888268383,
      "width": 308,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 506253427,
      "version": 38,
      "versionNonce": 372031314,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Patting (Port Forwarding) ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Patting (Port Forwarding) ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "QZoQzK0Te9e_s9xAy_kWT",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1509.3055350452655,
      "y": 92662.24875605937,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 415473277,
      "version": 322,
      "versionNonce": 1065293518,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Using this we allow users to come on our base system on a particular port number lets say 8080, when\nthey will come on this port number,we will route them on the port number of our nginx container or any\nother container which is lets say 80. because on this 80 my nginx is running.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Using this we allow users to come on our base system on a particular port number lets say 8080, when\nthey will come on this port number,we will route them on the port number of our nginx container or any\nother container which is lets say 80. because on this 80 my nginx is running.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "zZBO0klAswKOg4KGbfb7i",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1510.8608641594549,
      "y": 92772.25554711744,
      "width": 1111,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boN",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1107134397,
      "version": 291,
      "versionNonce": 1287456018,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker run -it -p 8080(base port):80(containerr port) nginx:latest\n\nthis allows us to have single system with multiple containers running different kind of services, one\nis running on 80(http) and other is running on 443(https)\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker run -it -p 8080(base port):80(containerr port) nginx:latest\n\nthis allows us to have single system with multiple containers running different kind of services, one\nis running on 80(http) and other is running on 443(https)\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "aFUr43zlvY-GvPLYs0WZH",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1342.492474257995,
      "y": 92972.55838571498,
      "width": 1023,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boO",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1861691876,
      "version": 114,
      "versionNonce": 760155406,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Everything that we were doing till now is a problem statement in itself, why it is a problem \nstatement -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Everything that we were doing till now is a problem statement in itself, why it is a problem \nstatement -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "fZSbBiSRUmv6PVqnNf6AZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1390.969036757995,
      "y": 93041.20291696498,
      "width": 1089,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boQ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1615767652,
      "version": 905,
      "versionNonce": 1555993298,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "It is a problem statement because, if we have to make change inside container, we have to manually\nsit, we have to create a container, go inside the container run some commands make the changes.\nmay be I have to go and install the software by myself, we have to go and open the port by myself,\neverything we are doing to create that image itself, Obviously docker run and other command those\nare linux command, They are using docker softwares but they are running on our base linux, But\neverything that is happening inside our container, that is not a command of our base linux, even\nafter being a linux command that is not the command in our base linux that is inside the container.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "It is a problem statement because, if we have to make change inside container, we have to manually\nsit, we have to create a container, go inside the container run some commands make the changes.\nmay be I have to go and install the software by myself, we have to go and open the port by myself,\neverything we are doing to create that image itself, Obviously docker run and other command those\nare linux command, They are using docker softwares but they are running on our base linux, But\neverything that is happening inside our container, that is not a command of our base linux, even\nafter being a linux command that is not the command in our base linux that is inside the container.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "2Et9TCpi9weigvDDdi7SD",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1396.965130507995,
      "y": 93266.92557321498,
      "width": 759,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boR",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 25179100,
      "version": 7,
      "versionNonce": 1111898958,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "So how do we automate the task that is running inside the container? ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "So how do we automate the task that is running inside the container? ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
