      "seed": 248931164,
      "version": 918,
      "versionNonce": 415787154,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "To automate that task or basically to create the image, why do we do it? we create a container, we \nmodify a container so that we can repackage it to a image, because once we have a image we can run\nany scripting to run any kind of container, But essencially what we need is we package this container\nto a image, To package a container into a image there are lot of manual effort that we have to do.\nSo reduce these manual effort we create something called as dockerfile.\nThe filename is always going to be dockerfile, no spaces, no capitalization, it will be same as\ndockerfile. due to name is same, hence we can put only one dockerfile insie one directory. So if we\nwant to create multiple dockerfile essencially they will be for different projects. So each project\nwill have its own directory, inside each directory we can have a dockerfile.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "To automate that task or basically to create the image, why do we do it? we create a container, we \nmodify a container so that we can repackage it to a image, because once we have a image we can run\nany scripting to run any kind of container, But essencially what we need is we package this container\nto a image, To package a container into a image there are lot of manual effort that we have to do.\nSo reduce these manual effort we create something called as dockerfile.\nThe filename is always going to be dockerfile, no spaces, no capitalization, it will be same as\ndockerfile. due to name is same, hence we can put only one dockerfile insie one directory. So if we\nwant to create multiple dockerfile essencially they will be for different projects. So each project\nwill have its own directory, inside each directory we can have a dockerfile.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "clN_Uor667hBYdUxFXljm",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1449.922161757995,
      "y": 93594.34744821498,
      "width": 429,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boT",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 223626844,
      "version": 51,
      "versionNonce": 79536526,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What do we write inside our dockerfile?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What do we write inside our dockerfile?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "_9La5LqXyFsbKU6PWiWmz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1512.222943007995,
      "y": 93631.98416696498,
      "width": 1001,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boU",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1802726364,
      "version": 210,
      "versionNonce": 1754367570,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "we write exactly the things that we do inside a container before we want to repack it to a \nimage. Exactly those things.\nThere are certain keywords that we use inside dockerfile.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "we write exactly the things that we do inside a container before we want to repack it to a \nimage. Exactly those things.\nThere are certain keywords that we use inside dockerfile.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "bjmz4opbaeaMzaUQMhak-",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1571.691693007995,
      "y": 93737.38651071498,
      "width": 264,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boV",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1104423388,
      "version": 135,
      "versionNonce": 1206796238,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "FROM python:3.9-slim\nWORKDIR /app \nCOPY ./app .\nRUN pip install flask\nEXPOSE 5000\nCMD [\"python\", \"app.py\"]\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "FROM python:3.9-slim\nWORKDIR /app \nCOPY ./app .\nRUN pip install flask\nEXPOSE 5000\nCMD [\"python\", \"app.py\"]\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "q3SvXCPWmR89A_hfhXjtC",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1493.086224257995,
      "y": 93969.96072946498,
      "width": 990,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boW",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 179373404,
      "version": 134,
      "versionNonce": 619768850,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Copy ./app -> means it will take app directory from outside our system and it will copy it\ninside container.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Copy ./app -> means it will take app directory from outside our system and it will copy it\ninside container.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "sdl2VcONpgr3M3Xbmga3O",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1497.902630507995,
      "y": 94076.65994821498,
      "width": 616,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boX",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 162893668,
      "version": 248,
      "versionNonce": 267458062,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "create dockerfile \n    and paste above\n\nadd one app folder and inside that create a file app.py\nprint(\"Hello world\")\n\ndocker build -t myapp .\ndocker run -it myapp:latest -> it will print Hello world",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "create dockerfile \n    and paste above\n\nadd one app folder and inside that create a file app.py\nprint(\"Hello world\")\n\ndocker build -t myapp .\ndocker run -it myapp:latest -> it will print Hello world",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "k15BekLz6LuKAWY5LNNmW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1418.328411757995,
      "y": 94351.58963571498,
      "width": 429,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
