    },
    {
      "id": "FYVGLKo4CBZcdejiDHnYQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1506.558880507995,
      "y": 94587.01932321498,
      "width": 1089,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bog",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1246047588,
      "version": 179,
      "versionNonce": 611225490,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "All these above commands are done on a running container, how these running containers are created?\nBetween all these steps we will see a temporary container",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "All these above commands are done on a running container, how these running containers are created?\nBetween all these steps we will see a temporary container",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "nSnuJ5h8GzBgBp3wMexYX",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1525.722943007995,
      "y": 94666.56229196498,
      "width": 1056,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boh",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1585167332,
      "version": 872,
      "versionNonce": 187787918,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "FROM python:3.9-slim\n\nmeans that we have to get a image of python:3.9-slim type from dockerhub create a container and\nrepack it as a temporary image Lets say I2,\nthis I2 for the next step, we will launch a container using I2 and we will perform \nWORKDIR /app action and then we will rapack this container into another image lets say I3\nand this I3 for the next step, we will launch a container using I3 and we will perform\nCOPY ./app . action and then we will rapack this container into another image lets say I4\nand this I4 for the next step, we will launch a container using I4 and we will perform, \nand so on, in between all the container are killed as work done thats why we are not able to see\ntemporary container. We will only see final image.\nand after all step we will get a final image file. this is we get as a output of this entire\nprocess or dockerfile.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "FROM python:3.9-slim\n\nmeans that we have to get a image of python:3.9-slim type from dockerhub create a container and\nrepack it as a temporary image Lets say I2,\nthis I2 for the next step, we will launch a container using I2 and we will perform \nWORKDIR /app action and then we will rapack this container into another image lets say I3\nand this I3 for the next step, we will launch a container using I3 and we will perform\nCOPY ./app . action and then we will rapack this container into another image lets say I4\nand this I4 for the next step, we will launch a container using I4 and we will perform, \nand so on, in between all the container are killed as work done thats why we are not able to see\ntemporary container. We will only see final image.\nand after all step we will get a final image file. this is we get as a output of this entire\nprocess or dockerfile.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
