    {
      "id": "HsTSQC0uAG2IRwIFA9aKT",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1522.023724257995,
      "y": 95465.66385446498,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 525,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bou",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1007847772,
      "version": 1290,
      "versionNonce": 1579755474,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Using above way, image is just passed to next step.\n\nSuppose we have to use flask, with flask multiple things are coming that are not going to use \nby us, so how we can insure only image of neccessary things are passed to next step, For that \nwe need to write our dockerfile in a very separate way, this thing is not heppening in our above\ndockerfile. It will include everything of flask even temporary file that we actually dont want.\nSo we will try to improve our dockerfile.\nthere are multiple ways to improvise our dockerfile,\none way is we can use smaller images like slim images of alpine images so use images as small as\npossible and build on top of it. Don't have even unnecessary binaries also.\nEverything that is needed install by ourself.\n\nSecond way ->\nLets say we have multiple RUN command, in that case what we can do is, we can run the commands like\nthis\n\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install __ && anything\nusing && we can run multiple RUN command benefit is all of this happening in a same layer, rather than\nhappening in different layers.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Using above way, image is just passed to next step.\n\nSuppose we have to use flask, with flask multiple things are coming that are not going to use \nby us, so how we can insure only image of neccessary things are passed to next step, For that \nwe need to write our dockerfile in a very separate way, this thing is not heppening in our above\ndockerfile. It will include everything of flask even temporary file that we actually dont want.\nSo we will try to improve our dockerfile.\nthere are multiple ways to improvise our dockerfile,\none way is we can use smaller images like slim images of alpine images so use images as small as\npossible and build on top of it. Don't have even unnecessary binaries also.\nEverything that is needed install by ourself.\n\nSecond way ->\nLets say we have multiple RUN command, in that case what we can do is, we can run the commands like\nthis\n\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install __ && anything\nusing && we can run multiple RUN command benefit is all of this happening in a same layer, rather than\nhappening in different layers.\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "9ORayvlEmoKQFgumHHAFa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1532.023724257995,
      "y": 96015.74588571498,
      "width": 1045,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
