    {
      "id": "Q3u2KDt8hAAsDLGiakGxK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1574.929974257995,
      "y": 96293.64432321498,
      "width": 1034,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "boy",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1563110108,
      "version": 1002,
      "versionNonce": 2018737294,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777685646399,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "First of all lets try what is happening over here\n\nLets say we have installed java, we have main file inside that we are using multiple things\nthese multiple things we are importing and these are our packages. Now if we will compile this\nwe will get executable here. executable is any kind of binary that our code creates, Once we\nhave that binary what I need that our container should stop here only, Now this should not be\nmy final container rather, I will make a new container over here, I will again give a FROM \nstatement, in this new container we will say that copy above binary and we will repack this\nnew container,\nSo one we are using to get our binary ready, bare minimum that we need\nAnother container will take this binary as an input and repack it to a new image now.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "First of all lets try what is happening over here\n\nLets say we have installed java, we have main file inside that we are using multiple things\nthese multiple things we are importing and these are our packages. Now if we will compile this\nwe will get executable here. executable is any kind of binary that our code creates, Once we\nhave that binary what I need that our container should stop here only, Now this should not be\nmy final container rather, I will make a new container over here, I will again give a FROM \nstatement, in this new container we will say that copy above binary and we will repack this\nnew container,\nSo one we are using to get our binary ready, bare minimum that we need\nAnother container will take this binary as an input and repack it to a new image now.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Ib46N6dOeCAhh7_nKUCiF",
      "type": "text",
